CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 20, 1941, pg. 22, reads: "The renovated and revitalized "Celebrity's Cafe," the former Coobus Club, on Centre avenue, is gaining in popularity, especially because of the fine small musical aggregation that swings out almost continually each evening.  The above visitors, from left to right, are: Miss Corien Davies from New York City, James Goode from Homestead, Miss Gladys Ford, who is attending Storer college; and Miss Frances Rose of the Smoky City. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Corien Davies, James Goode, Gladys Ford, and Frances Rosene, seated around two square tables with beverages, in Celebrity Cafe with Duquesne Beer clock, another version
